name: Attleboro Village
description:
Selected as one of the best communities by the Courier Times paper, Attleboro Retirement Village offers a wide variety of independent living and care-giving options. The 17 acre campus is located just north of Philadelphia and convenient to major roads, malls, and dining options. 

Residents may choose from three different living options that include independent living apartments, personal care at the Brunswick where staff provide comprehensive personal care, and skilled nursing for short and long term health needs. A fully secure memory care unit ensures that residents will have the support they need at all times. 

There are 134 apartment residences in the village’s three Victorian style residences, and the independent units come with studio, 1-bedroom, and 2-bedroom options. Each residence offers a full kitchen, a balcony, picture window, and individually controlled heating and air conditioning. Bi-weekly housekeeping, safety-enhanced bathrooms, and 24-hour medical response services ensure you will enjoy hassle-free living with peace of mind. 

Besides the convenience to local and regional shopping and dining options, residents will enjoy chef prepared meals and a wide array of daily activities, events, and classes. Main Street, the 25,000 square foot community pavilion, provides social options in several lounge areas, a theater, an auditorium, and a multipurpose activity room for club and group activities.
lifestyle: The Attleboro Village is a community of wonderful individuals who live a vibrant life with enthusiasm and meaning. Our residents are empowered by a culture of positive engagement, activity and social interaction.
entrance_fee_options: Yes, there is an entrance fee, but it is less than $25,000 (aka community fee).

name: Arbour Square of Harleysville
description:
Located in the scenic countryside outside of Philadelphia, Arbour Square of Harleysville offers a comfortable community experience that includes studio, one bedroom, and two bedroom apartments. The single fee for apartments also covers all utilities, three meals per day, and all maintenance and upkeep costs.

Mails are a highlight at Arbour Square, with summer meals complemented by the community’s own garden. Meals are customized to fit the dietary needs of residents, with low sodium and no sugar options available. 

Activities are regularly scheduled, including movie nights, lectures, and cultural events. Indoor and outdoor activities range from golf and walking groups, an onsite exercise room, a pass to the local YMCA, and exercise classes that include yoga and tai chi. An art studio, billiard room, and game room are just a few of the many other options that residents enjoy. 

A full spectrum of lifelong care is available, such as physical and occupational therapy, behavioral health services, audiology services, podiatry services, and geriatric primary care.

Arbour Square of Harleysville opened in 2016,  and offered a new option for seniors in Montgomery County – a rental community with no long-term lease or entrance fee.  In 2014, Arbour Square expanded to their existing 150 apartments  and added an additional 125 apartments and another 125,260 square feet of living area.
entrance_fee_options: Yes, there is an entrance fee, but it is less than $25,000 (aka community fee).

name: Cardinal Village
description:
Voted in 2017 as a Best of Assisted Living Award by SeniorAdvisor.com, Cardinal Village in Sewell, New Jersey values community and group events each week. Located just outside the Philadelphia suburbs, this continuing care retirement community has easy access to area malls, cultural events, and dining. 

There are a variety of floor plans that include studio and one bedroom units, as well as the option of having an outdoor patio. There are both independent living and assisted living options so that you can enjoy both the kind of lifestyle you value along with the security of having help for the daily tasks of each day. 

Meals are prepared to the tastes and dietary needs of residents with low sodium and low sugar options regularly in the mix. There is a large patio and deck area for events and outdoor dining, while meals are served in a stately dining room. A library on site provides regular access to popular titles, and a chapel is used daily by various religious groups.

Each day includes a variety of events that range from religious services to card groups to arts and crafts instruction.

name: Cathedral Village
description:
You’ll find a wide range of apartment floor plans and activities at Cathedral Village, a Continuing Care Retirement Community located just outside of downtown Philadelphia. Enjoy a swim in the pool, a stroll on the beautiful wooded campus, or relax with friends in one of the cozy gathering spaces. 
 
There is a full range of independent living and life care support options that include at-home services for in-home support, personal care, skilled nursing and rehabilitation, and memory support. It’s easy to travel to the doctor’s office from its central location, and it’s a short drive to area malls and shopping. 

Apartments range from simple studios at 340 square feet to spacious apartments of 1,300 square feet. Many units include the option of a terrace, patio, or balcony. Before you move in, the complimentary design service team will help you customize your apartment to meet your needs, and you’ll find updated appliances and a washer/dryer unit in most models. All apartments are pet friendly. 

If you want to stick around campus for the day, you’ll enjoy the fitness and aquatic center or the many group activities such as art classes. A computer lab ensures you always have high speed internet access and the campus also offers an on-site beauty salon and barber shop.
entrance_fee_options: Yes, there is an entrance fee required for all units.

name: Cokesbury Village
description:
The residences, grounds, and amenities are at the next level at Cokesbury Village in Hockessin, DE. This continuing care retirement community provides spacious, light-filled apartments in a variety of floor plans that connect to a tranquil campus in the beautiful Delaware countryside just to the west of Wilmington. 

This Cokesbury campus provides the financial security of an Acts' Type A Life Care Contract to all residents. In addition, all locations of Cokesbury Village are accredited by CARF International – the highest accreditation available to a CCRC. The Hockessin, DE location is close to area parks, cultural attractions, and other outdoor activities. 

Meals are served in several spacious, beautifully appointed dining rooms that include table service and lots of light. After your meal you may enjoy a stroll in the rolling fields on the campus that run along a bubbling stream and waterfall. Apartments are also pet-friendly. 

The extensive building and grounds include gardening areas, a card room, picnic area/gazebo, an art studio, wood workshop, sewing room, and billiard room, among many other rooms and interest groups. Art and music appreciation classes are regularly offered, and an auditorium regularly hosts events. A fitness room, heated indoor pool, and regular schedule of exercise classes offer plenty of opportunities to stay active
entrance_fee_options: Yes, there is an entrance fee required for all units.

name: Dunwoody Village
description:
Dunwoody Village, located just west of Philadelphia near the shopping and universities of the city’s Mainline area, offers a wide range of living arrangements, from studio apartments to 4,125 square foot townhomes in the community’s Penrose Carriage Homes. 

Shuttles are available for rides around the community’s 83 acre campus, for shopping trips, and doctor visits. Doctors and nurses are also available right within the community, and the range of care includes personalized nursing and a memory care wing with secure rooms and outdoor spaces. 

Townhomes at Dunwoody range from 2,105 square feet to 4,125 square feet and include two bedrooms, 2.5 baths, open floor plans, gas stoves and fireplaces, covered patios, two-car garages, and more than enough storage space. Apartment options include a studio, a junior bedroom, a one-bedroom or two-bedroom layout, and all have spacious closets and personal temperature controls.

Residents enjoy the tranquil views from their residences and the quiet surroundings, and the campus includes activity rooms, a heated pool, a jacuzzi, and a fitness center with a personal trainer. Meals can be enjoyed in a formal dining room, a casual dining area, or a takeout menu. One daily meal is included for each resident, with an option to purchase additional meals.

Fully enclosed, heated walkways make it easy to enjoy activities at the community building, even when the weather is cold, and the campus is supported by generators if the power goes out. The property offers emergency call systems and 24-hour security for added peace of mind.
refundability_options: Dunwoody Village offers a Non-Refundable Option, a 50% Refundable Option and a 100% Refundable Option for Penrose Homes
entrance_fee_options: Yes, there is an entrance fee required for all units.

name: Freedom Village at Brandywine
description:
From the cozy cafe/bistro to the spacious condominiums at Freedom Village, you’ll have the best in luxury and comfort all while living just down the road from Amish country. Freedom Village is still a short ride from Philadelphia and is close to area shopping and outdoor options. The campus includes an indoor pool, a wide variety of outdoor sports, walking paths, gardening, a wellness center, and a variety of rooms and meeting spaces for art classes or cultural events. 

This pet-friendly campus offers homes and condominiums that can be customized to your tastes and offer a significant amount of space, including four season rooms, patios/balconies, dens, and fully appointed kitchens. Floor plans include one bedroom and one bath all the way through two bedrooms with two baths, and each home offers generous living space and all of the conveniences you can imagine. 

There is an extensive range of independent living options and a beautiful dining room that comes with flexible meal plans. 

This early entry community offers a number of financial advantages for residents who sell their home, including discounts on healthcare, estate preservation, tax deductions, and very predictable long-term expenses. Freedom Village provides a life care guarantee. 

When it comes to providing lifelong care, residents can rest easy knowing that Freedom Village offers extensive care for memory loss, skilled nursing, personal care, and rehabilitation assistance.
refundability_options: Freedom Village's Traditional Plan is a life care contract that provides long term care in exchange for a non-refundable entrance fee. Freedom Village's Freedom Plan is a fee for service plan that provides for a 90% refund of the entrance fee.
entrance_fee_options: Yes, there is an entrance fee required for all units.

name: Friends Village at Woodstown
description:
A wide variety of holistic living options await at Friends Village in Woodstown, NJ where residents can enjoy an extensive range of innovative activities and choose between a wide variety of apartments and cottages that include all utilities and have several floor plans to choose between. 

At the heart of Friends Village is a commitment to life enrichment, including a certified music and memory program that helps residents reconnect with their memories to a familiar soundtrack. Staff work with residents to plan enrichment events that may include card games, book groups, exercise classes, or trips to cultural events in the Philadelphia or Wilmington region. Guest speakers and visiting performances round out a full activity calendar, and area clubs meet regularly on campus. 

A fitness center includes a medical director and access to physical or occupational therapy. Personal care, memory care, and skilled nursing are also offered as a full range of care for residents. 

Dining is always a highlight for residents, especially with an award-winning chef dreaming up imaginative and traditional dishes for meals in the restaurant-style dining room. The community center offers a library, art exhibition gallery, or social spaces to meet with friends in between meals.

description:
Located on 21 scenic acres a mere 30 minutes from downtown Philadelphia, Masonic Village in Lafayette Hill offers the quiet of the country near the delights of downtown. The Masonic Village offers a wide range of care, including skilled nursing and memory care, but it ensures residents enjoy excellent health with their broad range of activities and exercise options. 

Apartments include one and two bedroom options, as well as one and two bathrooms. Each unit has a living room, and a limited number have their own patios or balconies, although a spacious patio area is available to all residents.

name: Millcroft
description:
Enjoy the award-winning chef’s entrees in the formal dining room of Millcroft senior living or join friends for leisurely games in one of the many common spaces or game rooms. Millcroft Senior Living is located right in the middle of White Clay Creek State Park and is a short drive to Wilmington Delaware, offering the best of both worlds. 

There are extensive healthcare offerings at Millcroft, with spacious and comfortable independent living and assisted living apartments, in addition to skilled nursing care, rehabilitation services, and respite care. Staff are on hand 24 hours every day to meet the needs of residents. Staff provide transportation to appointments around town and also offer field trips to area attractions. 

Amenities include an exercise room, library, game room, in-house beauty/barber shop, and all-day dining. There are many fitness programs, clubs, groups, game/movie nights, and happy hour events regularly on the schedule. 

Residences range from efficient studio apartments through two bedroom units with functional kitchenettes. All utilities are included in your fees, as well as housekeeping and maintenance. The beautiful campus is landscaped for you, but residents have the option of keeping their own garden plots as well.

name: Pennswood Village
description:
Generously apportioned living areas and 82 acres of scenic paths and trails make Pennswood Village a truly unique Continuing Care Retirement Community in Newtown, PA. Founded with Quaker values of inclusion for all faiths, dignity, respect, and diversity, residents will find a warm and caring community. There are 10 spacious floor plans for apartments and homes on the property, with studio, one-bedroom, and two-bedroom options for residents. 

Residents will find many of the comforts and features they’ve grown to love in their own homes, including draperies, solid surface countertops, an over-the-range microwave, a dishwasher in many homes and a washer/dryer in all. There’s no shortage of space, from expanded closets to the options of patios or balconies on homes.  

Activities include walking or biking on the many trails, Tai Chi classes, yoga classes, and swimming in a 60 foot lap pool or a warm-water exercise pool. A fitness center includes personalized programs and guidance from fitness instructors. 

An interdenominational church service is provided each week, while rides to area churches are also provided. When residents require additional care and support, geriatricians and nurse practitioners will help provide a plan for the care each one requires, ensuring they have their needs met without increasing their costs.
entrance_fee_options: Yes, there is an entrance fee required for all units.

name: Peter Becker Community
description:
The Peter Becker Community CCRC provides a range of apartments and cottages just outside the village of Harleysville, PA and within a short drive of parks and malls. You’ll find everything you need for a full continuum of care from a highly trained and professional staff, offering independent living options, personal care, skilled nursing care, rehabilitation or memory care. 

Staff use the latest medical technology and are trained in the latest techniques for healthy living. Licensed registered nurses, nursing assistants, therapists, dietary specialists and activity coordinators offer a holistic retirement experience for all, and there’s always plenty to do. 

All residents have a membership to the on-campus YMCA, which includes an indoor aquatics center, a weight and exercise room, an indoor track, basketball courts, and fitness studios for a variety of classes such as yoga and zumba with licensed instructors. name: Phoebe Berks
description:
Phoebe Independent Living in Berks, PA is located in the rolling hills outside of Reading, PA and offers an extensive campus that includes nature trails, gardening plots, and a newly renovated pool and fitness center. There’s always plenty to do with life-enrichment programs, group meetings, social events, and easy access to area shopping, restaurants, and airports. 

Residents will have access to spiritual support from the onsite chaplain, while a bank, gift shop, and cafe on site offer convenient everyday services. A boardwalk with bocce, putting green, shuffleboard and outdoor gazebo are complemented by comfortable indoor lounges and activity rooms.

Besides having a pharmacy and a robust preventative care program, the Phoebe Berks community also provides personal care, skilled nursing, short and long term rehabilitation, memory support, and adult day services.

description:
You’ll find the widest range of living space options at Riddle Village where you can choose between a variety of one, two, and three bedroom apartments that offer numerous variations with extra bathrooms, dens, and other amenities. It goes without saying that these premier apartments offer the features most retirees desire: granite countertops, high quality cabinets, and stainless steel appliances. Each residence can also be customized through the choice of paint colors and closet layout. 

But the great amenities are just getting started in the floor plans. There’s also a fitness center with an indoor heated pool, a full-time fitness trainer, exercise classes, and a full time fitness trainer.

Meals are served in four unique dining venues by professionally trained chefs, and meals are available throughout the day. The campus includes many sitting areas and gathering spaces, bocce ball courts, and walking trails. Media, PA is minutes down the road, and the many attractions of Philadelphia are a short ride away. 

Riddle Village aims to offer lifecare at an affordable rate, with customizations such as skilled nursing, personal care, and memory care available. Residents who are no longer able to afford the costs of their care are often eligible for assistance through a variety of means to ensure that they are cared for at all times.

name: Rosemont Presbyterian Village
description:
Step back in time at the beautiful estate at Rosemont Presby’s Inspired Life continuing care retirement community. You’ll enjoy the sprawling 10 acre grounds that include woods with walking trails and renowned gardens that residents can help maintain. There is a central mansion that offers a grand ballroom, elegant dining, and plenty of classes and activities throughout each week. 

A grand veranda overlooks the flower, herb, and vegetable gardens for a casual day time chat, and year-round concerts, educational programs, and speakers fill up the evenings. Situated in a quiet residential neighborhood, residents enjoy a peaceful but active retirement lifestyle, taking walks or enjoying the onsite fitness center. Meals are prepared by a team of professional chefs who design menus based on the input of the resident dining committee. 

Residences include affordable 350-square-foot studios, one or two-bedroom apartments, and 900 or 1,800-square-foot cottages. All appliances are updated and modern, with high quality cabinets. Smaller units offer kitchenettes, while all include ample storage. 

Spiritual enrichment is a main feature at Rosemont Presby, and full life care is always available as needs change. Services include occupational therapy, short-term respite stays, hospice care, and personal care.

name: Shannondell At Valley Forge
description:
Located near parks, golf courses, and malls but convenient to major area highways, the Shannondell aims to provide a resort-like continuing care retirement community experience that is brimming full of activities and cultural enrichment opportunities. 

There are aquatics and fitness classes, college-level courses, performing arts rehearsals, arts & crafts instruction, card games, book clubs, gardening, and meditation groups meeting regularly. The fitness center offers a pool and a full complement of exercise machines. 

Since Shannondell is located on a 140 acre former farm, there is an abundance of natural beauty and scenery. Bird migrations ensure that a variety of wildlife pass through the area, while horses graze along the pastures of the community. 

Meals are served in formal dining rooms, buffets, bistros, and bakeries, and the health of residents is ensured by on-site physiologists and wellness nurses, as well as access to board-certified physicians with the Main Line Health and the Einstein Healthcare Network.

Continuing care is provided in the form of skilled nursing, long and short term rehabilitation, and memory care, ensuring that every resident has lifelong care and support.

name: Simpson House
description:
Located just outside Center City Philadelphia, the Simpson House provides the best of both worlds in its renovated apartments in a historic mansion on Olde Main and its latest building with 37 brand new apartments. Both buildings include new or freshly renovated open floor plan units that include studios, one bedroom and two bedroom options, as well as one and two bathrooms. 

Residents will enjoy the building’s old world charm combined with the latest kitchen finishes and appliance, spacious storage, and top notch interior design. Since you’re close to the city, you’ll have easy access to cultural events, shopping, the arts, and doctor’s appointments, but you’ll always have a cozy home to return to. 

The community center includes a wide variety of rooms and social spaces for games, groups meetings, and activities such as art classes. There is a pub dining room in addition to a formal dining space, and an auditorium hosts local events, music concerts, and the community’s own drama and choir groups. 

There is a wellness center on the campus as well as gardens and a community greenhouse. Worship services are available for a variety of denominations, including Catholic Mass, Methodist, Baptist, and Jewish services. 

For residents in need of additional care, there is short and long term rehabilitation, as well as personal care and skilled nursing. The memory support wing ensures that every need is taken care of by highly trained staff.

name: Spring Mill Presbyterian Village
description:
Located just outside Philadelphia, Spring Mill provides a convenient retirement location that is a short drive from downtown attractions, area shopping, or day trips to the nearby Lancaster region. The list of arts and culture event day trips is truly extensive, and the on-site clubs and activities ensure mental and physical well-being for all. 

Studio, one bedroom, and two bedroom apartments are fully updated with plush carpets and the latest safety features. Most residences include a modern kitchenette, and three meals per day are available in the community restaurant. 

There are flexible care options, with personal care available in independent living apartments, including if only one member of the household requires additional help. Residents will have the option of living in specially designed memory care apartments or in apartments that provide personal care whenever required. The community’s medical team includes including physicians, nurse practitioners and licensed nurses.

Services are provided via a simple monthly fee that covers all amenities so that there are no a la carte service surprises. The one time entrance fee is set at an affordable rate, and since Spring Mill is a nonprofit, residents can trust that they’ll be cared for even if their finances run out.

name: Ware Presbyterian Village
description:
Enjoy the beautiful Pennsylvania countryside and the resort-like atmosphere of Ware Presbyterian Village where residents of all faiths can enjoy both an extraordinary living space and financial peace of mind. Every resident undergoes an evaluation process that ensures they can afford their living arrangements, and should anything unexpected occur, everyone will receive the care they require. 

There are simple one and two bedroom apartments, apartments with one or two bedrooms that offer the option of a den, and larger villa one-two bedroom homes. Affordable apartment units offer walk-in closets, personal heating controls, fully equipped kitchens, and washer/dryer units.

A variety of clubs include a book club and bridge club, and residents enjoy the wood shop, crafts room, and art studio when they aren’t attending social events.

name: Westminster Village
description:
Westminster Village at Dover is a continuing care retirement community that also caters to the needs of adults who are 55 and older seeking independent living options. The community is located on 27 spacious acres and offers apartments and cottages to residents. 

As a nonprofit organization, Westminster Village puts the needs of residents front and center, offering competitive prices and a wide range of care. Personal care is available in a variety of settings, including in independent living cottages and apartments. Westminster has a 5 Star Rating from the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services (CMS), and a full life span of care includes in-home support, End of Life Care, Memory Support, and Skilled Nursing and Rehabilitation.

Residences include 1 bedroom/1 bath and 2 bedrooms/2 baths apartments, as well as a series of cottages that come in 2 bedrooms/1.5 baths through 2 bedrooms/2 baths arrangements. All residences have decks, modern kitchens with updated appliances, and plenty of storage space. 

One meal per day is included in most fee setups, but personal care residents receive three meals per day. Meals are served in a restaurant style dining room, and common areas offer opportunities to relax and socialize in between meals. 

The building includes a variety of rooms for activities, such as arts and crafts, billiards, church services, drama clubs, discussion groups, and game nights. Other groups go off-site, playing golf at local courses or attending cultural events nearby.

Just a short drive from Philadelphia’s shopping, restaurants, and hospitals, Wiley provides an active community lifestyle throughout its campus of private homes, walking trails, and common areas. 

A fitness center provides state of the art exercise equipment that is supervised by certified trainers. Rehabilitation for short and long also ensures residents are able to enjoy their daily tasks. name: Juniper Village at Bucks County
description:
Located on 20 beautiful acres in Bensalem, PA, just north of Philadelphia, Juniper Village Bucks County is an innovative continuing care retirement community that is consistently voted a top place to work and has a track record of cutting visits to the emergency room by over 50% compared to other populations. Doctors and health professionals are on call, and excellent, holistic healthcare is top priority for everyone on staff. 

Juniper Village just completed Phase I of their renovations, that include fabulous new community spaces, including a new outdoor deck, a two story lounge area with an open kitchen and many other upgrades.

The living options range from independent living, senior campus living, assisted living and personal care, memory care, short term rehab, long term rehab, and respite and fellowship services. Once you’re a part of Juniper Village, you’ll have long term security and peace of mind. 

You can spend your days walking the meandering trails throughout the campus or enjoying an art class with friends. Common areas offer opportunities for meet ups and conversations, while a large, modern outdoor patio is the ideal place to enjoy a meal or to have a drink in the evening. 

Juniper has a strong emphasis on environmentally friendly residences, and all floor plans include modern, fully updated appliances. Meals are prepared by a chef to be delicious but health conscious and adapted to meet dietary needs.
refundability_options: Juniper Village offers a Type A Contract that fully amortizes after 90 days. Prior to 90 days of residency it is 100% refundable. Juniper Village also offers a declining balance contract that fully amortizes over 3 years.
entrance_fee_options: Yes, there is an entrance fee required for all units.

name: The Atrium at Churchman Village
description:
Spacious, wide open, and light-filled are a few of the words that describe the Atrium at Churchman Village, a non-profit continuing care retirement community just outside of Wilmington, Delaware. Churchman Village specializes in providing a vibrant independent living community as well as rehabilitation services for short and long term needs. 

Apartments include studios with kitchenettes and one bedroom units that offer a kitchen with an oven, stove top, and refrigerator. Each unit connects to the large central gathering space in the Atrium, and all utilities, except phone and cable, are provided. Services and amenities include weekly housekeeping, bed linen, and complimentary personal laundry facilities. 

Residents will enjoy carefully planned, nutritious meals in an elegant dining room, while an activity room, patio and garden area, and common areas provide opportunities for recreation and conversation. Social and educational activities are regularly scheduled, and rides are available as needed, either for group events or personal appointments. 

The range of care options is quite wide at Churchman Village, including personal care, skilled nursing, respite care, palliative care, long term care, and hospice care.
entrance_fee_options: Yes, there is an entrance fee, but it is less than $25,000 (aka community fee).

name: Echo Lake
description:
Outdoor living, beautiful views, and a full range of shopping and lifestyle choices await at Echo Lake, a Continuing Care Retirement Community located near the Malvern, PA exit of the Pennsylvania Turnpike. From this tranquil lakeside retreat bordering a 70-acre nature preserve, you’ll also have easy access to the best shopping attractions in the region and cultural events in downtown Philadelphia. 

Modern, beautifully appointed dining rooms are splashed with light and offer perfect spaces to gather with friends or to enjoy a quiet meal. A pub and a cafe offer casual dining options, while the main dining room provides sophisticated and seasonal meals to meet every dietary need. 

A variety of outdoor activities are complemented by a 4500 square foot fitness center with all of the latest machines and fitness accessories. Common spaces are designed to encourage meetups and gatherings, while studios and activity rooms provide opportunities for art classes and other group activities. A library offers a quiet place to read, while an auditorium regularly hosts events. 

All housekeeping, landscaping and building maintenance are included and free you from daily chores, while you enjoy the assurance of additional care if you need it. Your community doesn’t change if you need additional nursing care or rehabilitation services.
entrance_fee_options: Yes, there is an entrance fee, but it is less than $25,000 (aka community fee).

name: Masonic Village at Burlington
description:
Located just outside the Philadelphia metro area, the Masonic Village campus in Burlington, New Jersey provides 450 pristine acres that offer walking paths, putting greens, and landscaped grounds that residents of this continuing care retirement community can enjoy at their leisure. There is no shortage of exciting activities, from creative arts, to gardening to wellness classes at the fitness center. 

An attentive staff and 24-hour security ensure that residents are completely safe, while newly constructed cottages are ideal for independent living in a modern, fully updated home. All maintenance and upkeep are provided by staff, and the majority of expenses and services are covered by monthly fees. 

Cottages come in two models with approximately 2,300 and 1,900 square feet, and they provide a garage, two bedrooms, a den, a sunroom, two bathrooms, and an eat-in kitchen. A patio and front porch are ideal for outdoor living. 

Apartments are also generous in their space, with the deluxe two-bedroom, two-bath units providing almost 1,000 square feet, while the one-bedroom, one units offer a simpler yet functional living option. 

When residents require skilled nursing, memory care, or rehabilitation, they’ll find everything they need right on campus. In the event of a financial crisis, Masonic Village also offers financial assistance.
entrance_fee_options: Yes, there is an entrance fee, but it is less than $25,000 (aka community fee).

name: Shipley Manor
description:
Shipley Manor offers the best of all worlds, with convenient access to downtown Wilmington, Delaware, short drives to the rolling hills of Pennsylvania, or the ease of shopping and dining at area malls. This five-star rated continuing care retirement community offers both independent living options and a full continuum of care: skilled nursing home care, rehabilitation services, and respite/short stays.

The beautifully landscaped campus is close to parks and golf courses, ensuring that residents enjoy a lot of time outside. A health center, library, exercise classes, and resident groups and clubs offer plenty of activities no matter what the weather is like outside. 

Each meal is planned by a professional executive chef and is served in a bright and cheerful fine dining room. Lounges throughout the facility accommodate happy hours and other resident events. 

Shipley Manor provides transportation to area events and to medical appointments, and many residents choose to bring their pets along, including multiple pets and large breed dogs.

name: St. Mary Villa
description:
Attend Catholic mass daily, enjoy attentive spiritual care, and find quiet moments in the community chapel of St. Mary Villa. Located near downtown Landsdale and close to area shopping and dining, you’ll have easy access to everything you need while enjoying the peaceful, spiritually rich surroundings of this continuing care retirement community. 

Independent living is an important aspect of living at St. Mary Villa, with bright, sun-filled one-bedroom apartments offering both comfort and security. Medical and personal care is available 24/7, and all maintenance is provided. Each residence has a patio, stainless steel appliances, a spa shower, and a wash/dryer combo. Housekeeping and linen services are provided weekly. 

Three meals per day are served in a restaurant style dining room where each plate is designed to meet the dietary needs of residents. In addition, there’s always a snack center with drinks available. Residents may enjoy some social time in the facility game room in between meals, pick up a book at the library, or meet up with friends in one of the lounges. 

Rooms are available for short term rehabilitation stays, and all residents can benefit from the attentiveness of memory care or personal care services when needed.
